~ start
Hyena: Hehehe! Look at this, boys... a "man-cub" wandering where the shadows don't reach.
Hyena: You look skinny, traveler. Not even enough meat on those bones to make a decent stew for the pack!
Hyena: Are you lost? Or just looking for someone to laugh at your misery? Hehehe!

- I'm looking for the inhabitants.
	Hyena: Inhabitants? You mean the "VIPs" of this rock? 
	Hyena: Keep looking, little morsel. I'm just here for the leftovers. 
	Hyena: I don't "belong" to any census, and I certainly don't take orders from a lighthouse.
	=> END

- Why so much laughing?
	Hyena: Because life is a joke, and you’re the punchline! 
	Hyena: Now run along before I decide you look better as a snack than as a conversation partner.
	=> END

- Leave me alone, scavenger.
	Hyena: Ooh, "scavenger"! Someone’s been reading the dictionary. 
	Hyena: Go on, keep your secrets. The desert knows how to keep them better than you.
	=> END